text: Hi Cherry, how are you today?
Not very good, I’m really worried.
Why?
Because I’ve been thinking about all the things I have to do this semester.
Like what?
Like all the projects, cram school, homework, tests...
Oh, I see.
I feel so much pressure.
I think about it all the time.
Even in the morning I wake up worried
that I forgot to do something.
Cherry, you are a very smart student.
You don’t need to worry about all those things.
Just do your best every day
and I know you will be happy with the result.
Thanks Allen.
I'll try not to worry and do my best.
I feel a little better already!
Proverbs says,
Worry weighs a person down,
but an encouraging word cheers a person up.
